@startuml

title Inventory Admin Statistics Report Sequence Diagram

actor "Inventory Admin" as Admin
participant "Frontend Website" as Frontend
participant "Apache\n(HTTP Server)" as Apache

box "Laravel Application" #LightGreen
  participant "Middleware" as MW
  participant "InventoryStatisticsController" as ISC
  participant "Eloquent ORM" as ORM
  participant "DOM PDF Engine" as PDF
end box

database "MariaDB Database" as DB

note right of Admin
Inventory Admin can view inventory
statistics, apply monthly or annual
filters, and export the resulting
report as CSV or PDF.
end note

note left of DB
It is assumed the Inventory Admin is
authenticated/authorized unless an exception occurs.
end note


== View Statistics Report ==

Admin -> Frontend: Open statistics page or change report filters
activate Admin
activate Frontend
activate Apache
activate MW
activate ISC
activate ORM
activate PDF
activate DB

Frontend -> Apache: GET /inventory_management/inventory_statistics?type=&year=&month=

alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP statistics page request
else Route not found
    Apache --> Frontend: 404 Not Found
    Frontend --> Admin: Display "Inventory statistics route not found" error
end

alt Valid + Authorized
    MW -> ISC: Pass authenticated and authorized statistics request
else Validation/Auth error
    MW --> Frontend: 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden
    Frontend --> Admin: Display validation or authorization error
end

ISC -> ISC: Read type, year, and month from request

alt Monthly report selected
    ISC -> ORM: Query lending/lending_items/equipment data filtered by selected month and year
    ORM -> DB: SELECT aggregated item request counts WHERE MONTH(start_time) = ? AND YEAR(start_time) = ?
else Annual report selected
    ISC -> ORM: Query lending/lending_items/equipment data filtered by selected year
    ORM -> DB: SELECT aggregated item request counts WHERE YEAR(start_time) = ?
end

alt Statistics query success
    DB --> ORM: Aggregated statistics result set
    ORM --> ISC: items collection with description and total
else Statistics query failure
    DB --> ORM: Query failed / SQL exception
    ORM --> ISC: Statistics retrieval failed
    ISC --> Frontend: 500 Internal Server Error
    Frontend --> Admin: Display system error while loading statistics
end

ISC -> ISC: topItem = first ranked item or null
ISC -> ISC: totalReqs = sum of request totals
ISC -> ISC: totalItems = count of analyzed items

ISC -> ORM: Query available report years from lending statistics dataset
ORM -> DB: SELECT DISTINCT available years used in statistics

alt Available years query success
    DB --> ORM: Available year list
    ORM --> ISC: availableYears collection
    ISC --> Frontend: Return inventory statistics view with chart data and summaries
    Frontend --> Admin: Display statistics cards, chart, and top 3 table
else Available years query failure
    DB --> ORM: Query failed / SQL exception
    ORM --> ISC: Available year retrieval failed
    ISC --> Frontend: 500 Internal Server Error
    Frontend --> Admin: Display system error while loading available years
end


== Export CSV Statistics Report ==

Admin -> Frontend: Click "Exportar a CSV"
Frontend -> Apache: GET /inventory_management/inventory_statistics/export?format=csv&type=&year=&month=

alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP CSV export request
else Route not found
    Apache --> Frontend: 404 Not Found
    Frontend --> Admin: Display "Statistics export route not found" error
end

alt Valid + Authorized
    MW -> ISC: Pass authenticated and authorized CSV export request
else Validation/Auth error
    MW --> Frontend: 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden
    Frontend --> Admin: Display validation or authorization error
end

ISC -> ISC: Read format, type, year, and month from request

alt CSV format selected
    ISC -> ORM: Re-run filtered statistics aggregation for export dataset
    ORM -> DB: SELECT aggregated item request counts for CSV export
else Invalid export format
    ISC --> Frontend: 422 Unprocessable Entity / 400 Bad Request
    Frontend --> Admin: Display invalid export format error
end

alt CSV export query success
    DB --> ORM: Aggregated export result set
    ORM --> ISC: Export dataset ready
    ISC -> ISC: Build CSV filename and stream CSV response
    ISC --> Frontend: Return downloadable CSV response
    Frontend --> Admin: Download CSV file message "Tu documento se descargará en unos instantes."
else CSV export query failure
    DB --> ORM: Query failed / SQL exception
    ORM --> ISC: CSV export retrieval failed
    ISC --> Frontend: 500 Internal Server Error
    Frontend --> Admin: Display system error while exporting CSV statistics
end


== Export PDF Statistics Report ==

Admin -> Frontend: Click "Exportar a PDF"
Frontend -> Apache: GET /inventory_management/inventory_statistics/export?format=pdf&type=&year=&month=

alt Route exists
    Apache -> MW: Forward HTTP PDF export request
else Route not found
    Apache --> Frontend: 404 Not Found
    Frontend --> Admin: Display "Statistics export route not found" error
end

alt Valid + Authorized
    MW -> ISC: Pass authenticated and authorized PDF export request
else Validation/Auth error
    MW --> Frontend: 401 Unauthorized / 403 Forbidden
    Frontend --> Admin: Display validation or authorization error
end

ISC -> ISC: Read format, type, year, and month from request

alt PDF format selected
    ISC -> ORM: Re-run filtered statistics aggregation for export dataset
    ORM -> DB: SELECT aggregated item request counts for PDF export
else Invalid export format
    ISC --> Frontend: 422 Unprocessable Entity / 400 Bad Request
    Frontend --> Admin: Display invalid export format error
end

alt PDF export query success
    DB --> ORM: Aggregated export result set
    ORM --> ISC: Export dataset ready

    ISC -> ISC: Compute summary values for PDF report
    ISC -> PDF: Render statistics PDF view with filtered data

    alt PDF render success
        PDF --> ISC: PDF document generated
        ISC --> Frontend: Return downloadable PDF response
        Frontend --> Admin: Download PDF file and message "Tu documento se descargará en unos instantes."
    else PDF render failure
        PDF --> ISC: PDF generation failed / rendering exception
        ISC --> Frontend: 500 Internal Server Error
        Frontend --> Admin: Display system error while generating PDF statistics
    end

else PDF export query failure
    DB --> ORM: Query failed / SQL exception
    ORM --> ISC: PDF export retrieval failed
    ISC --> Frontend: 500 Internal Server Error
    Frontend --> Admin: Display system error while exporting PDF statistics
end

@enduml